    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Moses",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 5,
        "summary": "Adam and Eve bring forth children\u2014Adam offers sacrifice and serves God\u2014Cain and Abel are born\u2014Cain rebels, loves Satan more than God, and becomes Perdition\u2014Murder and wickedness spread\u2014The gospel is preached from the beginning.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that after I, the Lord God, had driven them out, that Adam began to till the earth, and to have dominion over all the beasts of the field, and to eat his bread by the sweat of his brow, as I the Lord had commanded him. And Eve, also, his wife, did labor with him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 2:26.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 4:25.",
                        "start": 200,
                        "end": 204
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Labor.",
                        "start": 268,
                        "end": 273
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Adam knew his wife, and she bare unto him sons and daughters, and they began to multiply and to replenish the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 5:4 (3\u201332).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:1 (1\u20132); Moses 5:16 (16\u201317).",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 138:39.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 9:1; Moses 2:28.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And from that time forth, the sons and daughters of Adam began to divide two and two in the land, and to till the land, and to tend flocks, and they also begat sons and daughters.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:17; Moses 5:28.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Adam and Eve, his wife, called upon the name of the Lord, and they heard the voice of the Lord from the way toward the Garden of Eden, speaking unto them, and they saw him not; for they were shut out from his presence.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:26; Moses 6:4.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Eden.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 137
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 42:9.",
                        "start": 213,
                        "end": 221
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p4",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he gave unto them commandments, that they should worship the Lord their God, and should offer the firstlings of their flocks, for an offering unto the Lord. And Adam was obedient unto the commandments of the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Worship.",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 13:12 (12\u201313); Num. 18:17; Mosiah 2:3. TG\u00a0Firstborn.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 112
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:19 (19\u201320).",
                        "start": 122,
                        "end": 128
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Obedience.",
                        "start": 174,
                        "end": 182
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And after many days an angel of the Lord appeared unto Adam, saying: Why dost thou offer sacrifices unto the Lord? And Adam said unto him: I know not, save the Lord commanded me.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Angels.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Ordinance; Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And then the angel spake, saying: This thing is a similitude of the sacrifice of the Only Begotten of the Father, which is full of grace and truth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Types of, in Anticipation.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:5 (3\u20137); 1\u00a0Chr. 6:49; Alma 34:10 (10\u201315); Moses 5:21 (20\u201326). TG\u00a0Blood, Symbolism of; Jesus Christ, Atonement through.",
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:32. TG\u00a0Grace.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 136
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:6.",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 146
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore, thou shalt do all that thou doest in the name of the Son, and thou shalt repent and call upon God in the name of the Son forevermore.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 1:17.",
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 6:57; 7:10. TG\u00a0Repent.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 90
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prayer.",
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And in that day the Holy Ghost fell upon Adam, which beareth record of the Father and the Son, saying: I am the Only Begotten of the Father from the beginning, henceforth and forever, that as thou hast fallen thou mayest be redeemed, and all mankind, even as many as will.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Holy Ghost, Baptism of.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 125
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Death, Spiritual, First; Fall of Man.",
                        "start": 202,
                        "end": 208
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 49:15; Mosiah 27:24 (24\u201326); D&C 93:38; A\u00a0of\u00a0F 1:3. TG\u00a0Redemption; Salvation, Plan of.",
                        "start": 224,
                        "end": 232
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 12
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And in that day Adam blessed God and was filled, and began to prophesy concerning all the families of the earth, saying: Blessed be the name of God, for because of my transgression my eyes are opened, and in this life I shall have joy, and again in the flesh I shall see God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Man, New, Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 107:56 (41\u201356).",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Transgress.",
                        "start": 167,
                        "end": 180
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 3:5 (3\u20136); D&C 76:12 (12, 19); Moses 4:11 (10\u201313).",
                        "start": 184,
                        "end": 188
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Joy.",
                        "start": 231,
                        "end": 234
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 19:26; 2\u00a0Ne. 9:4.",
                        "start": 253,
                        "end": 258
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Eve, his wife, heard all these things and was glad, saying: Were it not for our transgression we never should have had seed, and never should have known good and evil, and the joy of our redemption, and the eternal life which God giveth unto all the obedient.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 2:23 (22\u201325). TG\u00a0Birth Control; Family; Marriage, Motherhood.",
                        "start": 123,
                        "end": 127
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 3:22.",
                        "start": 151,
                        "end": 156
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Adam and Eve blessed the name of God, and they made all things known unto their sons and their daughters.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 3:20; D&C 138:39.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 4:9 (9\u201310).",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
                        "data-pointer-type": "media",
                        "data-scroll-id": "p12",
                        "title": "Associated Content"
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Satan came among them, saying: I am also a son of God; and he commanded them, saying: Believe it not; and they believed it not, and they loved Satan more than God. And men began from that time forth to be carnal, sensual, and devilish.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Devil.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Spiritual Blindness; Unbelief.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 97
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:28; 6:15.",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 146
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Carnal Mind; Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn.",
                        "start": 209,
                        "end": 215
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord God called upon men by the Holy Ghost everywhere and commanded them that they should repent;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 14:26 (16\u201326).",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And as many as believed in the Son, and repented of their sins, should be saved; and as many as believed not and repented not, should be damned; and the words went forth out of the mouth of God in a firm decree; wherefore they must be fulfilled.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Faith.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Savior.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 42:60.",
                        "start": 137,
                        "end": 143
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Adam and Eve, his wife, ceased not to call upon God. And Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bare Cain, and said: I have gotten a man from the Lord; wherefore he may not reject his words. But behold, Cain hearkened not, saying: Who is the Lord that I should know him?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:1 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 112,
                        "end": 116
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 3:13; 1\u00a0Ne. 2:12 (12\u201313); Mosiah 27:8 (7\u201337).",
                        "start": 219,
                        "end": 228
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 5:2; Alma 9:6.",
                        "start": 272,
                        "end": 276
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And she again conceived and bare his brother Abel. And Abel hearkened unto the voice of the Lord. And Abel was a keeper of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Heb. 11:4.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 138:40.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Cain loved Satan more than God. And Satan commanded him, saying: Make an offering unto the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 10:21 (20\u201321).",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 132:9 (8\u201311).",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And in process of time it came to pass that Cain brought of the fruit of the ground an offering unto the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:5.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Abel, he also brought of the firstlings of his flock, and of the fat thereof. And the Lord had respect unto Abel, and to his offering;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 2:3.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Respect.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 106
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 137
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But unto Cain, and to his offering, he had not respect. Now Satan knew this, and it pleased him. And Cain was very wroth, and his countenance fell.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:5 (3\u20137); Moses 5:7 (4\u20138).",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 7:26.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord said unto Cain: Why art thou wroth? Why is thy countenance fallen?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If thou doest well, thou shalt be accepted. And if thou doest not well, sin lieth at the door, and Satan desireth to have thee; and except thou shalt hearken unto my commandments, I will deliver thee up, and it shall be unto thee according to his desire. And thou shalt rule over him;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:7; D&C 52:15; 97:8; 132:50.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:7.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 113
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bondage, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 187,
                        "end": 194
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:30.",
                        "start": 270,
                        "end": 274
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 13
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For from this time forth thou shalt be the father of his lies; thou shalt be called Perdition; for thou wast also before the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honesty.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 76:26, 32 (32\u201348). TG\u00a0Sons of Perdition.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 4:1.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 120
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall be said in time to come\u2014That these abominations were had from Cain; for he rejected the greater counsel which was had from God; and this is a cursing which I will put upon thee, except thou repent.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 6:27 (26\u201328).",
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 79
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:36. TG\u00a0Curse.",
                        "start": 155,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Cain was wroth, and listened not any more to the voice of the Lord, neither to Abel, his brother, who walked in holiness before the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Adam and his wife mourned before the Lord, because of Cain and his brethren.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mourning.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it came to pass that Cain took one of his brothers' daughters to wife, and they loved Satan more than God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:3 (2\u20133).",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 73
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:13.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Satan said unto Cain: Swear unto me by thy throat, and if thou tell it thou shalt die; and swear thy brethren by their heads, and by the living God, that they tell it not; for if they tell it, they shall surely die; and this that thy father may not know it; and this day I will deliver thy brother Abel into thine hands.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 5:36.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Satan sware unto Cain that he would do according to his commands. And all these things were done in secret.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 5:23.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Cain said: Truly I am Mahan, the master of this great secret, that I may murder and get gain. Wherefore Cain was called Master Mahan, and he gloried in his wickedness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 27:24.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Murder.",
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 27:25.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0\u201cMind,\u201d \u201cdestroyer,\u201d and \u201cgreat one\u201d are possible meanings of the roots evident in \u201cMahan.\u201d",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 136
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Cain went into the field, and Cain talked with Abel, his brother. And it came to pass that while they were in the field, Cain rose up against Abel, his brother, and slew him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Cain gloried in that which he had done, saying: I am free; surely the flocks of my brother falleth into my hands.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Boast.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covet.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord said unto Cain: Where is Abel, thy brother? And he said: I know not. Am I my brother's keeper?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:9 (8\u201315).",
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the Lord said: What hast thou done? The voice of thy brother's blood cries unto me from the ground.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Life, Sanctity of.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And now thou shalt be cursed from the earth which hath opened her mouth to receive thy brother's blood from thy hand.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 29:41. TG\u00a0Curse.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When thou tillest the ground it shall not henceforth yield unto thee her strength. A fugitive and a vagabond shalt thou be in the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strength.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:12 (11\u201312).",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Cain said unto the Lord: Satan tempted me because of my brother's flocks. And I was wroth also; for his offering thou didst accept and not mine; my punishment is greater than I can bear.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covet; Temptation.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Punish.",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Behold thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the Lord, and from thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond in the earth; and it shall come to pass, that he that findeth me will slay me, because of mine iniquities, for these things are not hid from the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I the Lord said unto him: Whosoever slayeth thee, vengeance shall be taken on him sevenfold. And I the Lord set a mark upon Cain, lest any finding him should kill him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:15; Alma 3:7 (7\u201316).",
                        "start": 118,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 14
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Cain was shut out from the presence of the Lord, and with his wife and many of his brethren dwelt in the land of Nod, on the east of Eden.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bondage, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 6:49.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Cain knew his wife, and she conceived and bare Enoch, and he also begat many sons and daughters. And he builded a city, and he called the name of the city after the name of his son, Enoch.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0There was a man named Enoch in Cain's lineage, and a city by that name among his people. Do not confuse these with the Enoch of the righteous line of Seth and with his city, Zion, also called \u201cCity of Enoch.\u201d",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 158
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And unto Enoch was born Irad, and other sons and daughters. And Irad begat Mahujael, and other sons and daughters. And Mahujael begat Methusael, and other sons and daughters. And Methusael begat Lamech.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Lamech took unto himself two wives; the name of one being Adah, and the name of the other, Zillah.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Adah bare Jabal; he was the father of such as dwell in tents, and they were keepers of cattle; and his brother's name was Jubal, who was the father of all such as handle the harp and organ.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 6:38; 7:5 (5\u20136).",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Zillah, she also bare Tubal Cain, an instructor of every artificer in brass and iron. And the sister of Tubal Cain was called Naamah.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Lamech said unto his wives, Adah and Zillah: Hear my voice, ye wives of Lamech, hearken unto my speech; for I have slain a man to my wounding, and a young man to my hurt.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "If Cain shall be avenged sevenfold, truly Lamech shall be seventy and seven fold;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Lamech presumptively boasted that far more would be done for him than for Cain. The reasons for his assumption are given in verses\u00a049 and 50.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For Lamech having entered into a covenant with Satan, after the manner of Cain, wherein he became Master Mahan, master of that great secret which was administered unto Cain by Satan; and Irad, the son of Enoch, having known their secret, began to reveal it unto the sons of Adam;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 4:24.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 10
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore Lamech, being angry, slew him, not like unto Cain, his brother Abel, for the sake of getting gain, but he slew him for the oath's sake.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Oath.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 139
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For, from the days of Cain, there was a secret combination, and their works were in the dark, and they knew every man his brother.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Secret Combinations.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 58
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore the Lord cursed Lamech, and his house, and all them that had covenanted with Satan; for they kept not the commandments of God, and it displeased God, and he ministered not unto them, and their works were abominations, and began to spread among all the sons of men. And it was among the sons of men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Curse.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 8:14 (14\u201315, 19).",
                        "start": 262,
                        "end": 266
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And among the daughters of men these things were not spoken, because that Lamech had spoken the secret unto his wives, and they rebelled against him, and declared these things abroad, and had not compassion;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Wherefore Lamech was despised, and cast out, and came not among the sons of men, lest he should die.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thus the works of darkness began to prevail among all the sons of men.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Darkness, Spiritual.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And God cursed the earth with a sore curse, and was angry with the wicked, with all the sons of men whom he had made;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Earth, Curse of.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For they would not hearken unto his voice, nor believe on his Only Begotten Son, even him whom he declared should come in the meridian of time, who was prepared from before the foundation of the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Disobedience; Unbelief.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moses 7:46. TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Birth of.",
                        "start": 114,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Authority of.",
                        "start": 152,
                        "end": 160
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thus the Gospel began to be preached, from the beginning, being declared by holy angels sent forth from the presence of God, and by his own voice, and by the gift of the Holy Ghost.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gospel.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Preaching.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 12:29 (28\u201330); Moro. 7:25 (25, 31).",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 7:53.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thus all things were confirmed unto Adam, by an holy ordinance, and the Gospel preached, and a decree sent forth, that it should be in the world, until the end thereof; and thus it was. Amen.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Adam.",
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}